# Help Materials Architecture Rule

This workspace uses a mandatory dual model for each domain (`linux`, `sql`, and future domains) under `docs/`:
- `topics/` for canonical topic content (source of truth).
- `learning/`, `cheatsheets/`, `recipes/` for usage modes.

## Core Intent
- Build practical reference materials for different audiences.
- Keep content easy to navigate by both topic and consumption mode.
- Prevent duplication as the project grows.

## Required Structure For Every Domain
- `docs/<domain>/README.md`
- `docs/<domain>/topics/<topic>/README.md`
- `docs/<domain>/learning/*.md`
- `docs/<domain>/cheatsheets/*.md`
- `docs/<domain>/recipes/*.md`

## Authoring Rules
- Put full explanations in `topics/*`.
- In `learning/cheatsheets/recipes`, keep focused summaries and link back to `topics/*`.
- Each `topics/<topic>/README.md` must include a "Где использовать" section with links to related mode files.
- Prefer links over copied text when overlapping content appears.

## Growth Rules
- Add new domains using the same folder contract.
- Add new topics as new `topics/<topic>/README.md` modules.
- Keep naming stable and descriptive; avoid ad-hoc files in domain root.
- Update `docs/PROJECT_APPROACHES.md` when architecture-level decisions change.

## Default Agent Behavior On Content Requests
- If user asks to "add a new topic" for a domain, create:
  - `<domain>/topics/<topic>/README.md`
  - At least one related mode file update in `learning/`, `cheatsheets/`, or `recipes/` with links.
- If user asks to "add content", update canonical explanation in `topics/*` first, then add or update mode-specific summaries.
- Always preserve bidirectional linking:
  - `topics/*` -> "Где использовать" -> mode files
  - mode files -> "См. тематические источники" -> `topics/*`
- Prefer extending existing files before creating new files for near-duplicate scope.

## Markdown Content Contract
- Every substantial content page should include, when applicable:
  - `# Title`
  - `## Цель`
  - `## Когда использовать`
  - `## Пошаговый подход`
  - `## Примеры`
  - `## Частые ошибки`
  - `## Проверка результата`
  - `## Связанные материалы`
- Keep pages practical and concise; avoid long theory dumps without examples.

## Build And Publish Contract
- Markdown is the source of truth. Do not manually maintain parallel HTML copies.
- Use MkDocs Material workflow:
  - local preview: `mkdocs serve`
  - build: `mkdocs build`
  - publish: GitHub Actions workflow for Pages
